        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The variance is the average of the squared deviations from the mean,\ni.e.,  "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "var = mean(abs(x - x.mean())**2)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The mean is normally calculated as "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "x.sum() / N"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", where "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "N = len(x)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ".\nIf, however, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ddof"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is specified, the divisor "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "N - ddof"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is used\ninstead.  In standard statistical practice, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ddof=1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " provides an\nunbiased estimator of the variance of a hypothetical infinite\npopulation.  "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ddof=0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " provides a maximum likelihood estimate of the\nvariance for normally distributed variables."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Note that for complex numbers, the absolute value is taken before\nsquaring, so that the result is always real and nonnegative."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "For floating-point input, the variance is computed using the same\nprecision the input has.  Depending on the input data, this can cause\nthe results to be inaccurate, especially for "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "float32"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " (see example\nbelow).  Specifying a higher-accuracy accumulator using the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "dtype"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nkeyword can alleviate this issue."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "For this function to work on sub-classes of ndarray, they must define\n"
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/sum",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "sum",
                "text": "sum"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " with the kwarg "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "keepdims"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
